Company Description: Solutia Traces Its Roots Back To 1901 And The Founding Of The Monsanto Company. Solutia Carries Out Its Operations Through Approximately 60 Locations IN More Than 30 Countries. The Company Employs Nearly 6,000 People At These Sites. Solutia Maintains A Location IN Greenwood, S.C.

Company Description: Welcome To Bryant Pharmacy While Growing Up IN Sylvania, Georgia, Cliff Bryant Worked Part-Time At A Local Drugstore. At The Time, The Corner Drugstore Was More Than Just A Pharmacy, It Was A Social Place Where You Could Get A Milkshake, Cokes, Peanuts And Even Do Some Gift Shopping. Customers There Were Greeted By Name And Service Was A Priority. 'mrs. Smith' Could Simply Ask For Her 'blue Blood Pressure Pills, ' And The Pharmacist Would Know Just What She Needed. IN 1964, Mr. Bryant Purchased Smith Drugs No. 2 IN Anderson, SC And His Vision Of Carrying On The Service And Quality Of A Local Drugstore Became A Reality. He Offered A Full-Service Fountain, Assorted Gifts And A Pharmacy That Included Free Delivery. IN The 1990's, The Name Of The Store Was Changed To Bryant Pharmacy & Supply. With The New Name Came A New Emphasis On Durable Medical Equipment And Supplies. To Develop This Dme Department, Giles Canter Came On Board. Mr Canter Has Built A Service-Centered Operation Reaching Far Into Neighboring Communities While Maintaining That Personal Touch Mr. Bryant Began With. Bryant Pharmacy & Supply Is Now A Full-Service Medical Equipment Supplier Specializing IN Custom Mobility Devices And Lifts, Home_respiratory And Sleep Equipment, As Well As Diabetic Testing Supplies. Currently, Cliff, His Three Sons, ( Craig, Kendall, And Kevin ), And Giles Carry On The Business With The Same Philosophy As It Began. But Even After All These Years, Service Is The Priority, Delivery Is Still Free And 'mrs. Smith' Can Still Get A Coke And Simply Ask For Her 'blue Pills!'

Company Description: Defined Source Cooperative Defined Source Cooperative (Dsc), Inc. Is A Field Service Consulting Firm Whose Headquarters Are Based IN Philadelphia With Additional Offices IN Locations Including South Carolina And Canada. Dsc's Charter Is To Provide The Highest Quality Of Field-Technical And Management Professionals (As Well As Teams) To The Power Generation Industry And Other Industrial Markets Worldwide. Dsc Concentrates Its Efforts Exclusively IN The Areas Of Development, Engineering, Construction, Commissioning, Operations, Maintenance And Aftermarket Service. Company Description: Looking For Top-Of-The-Line Electrical Supplies And Custom Commercial Lighting Services? Graybar Greenville Is A Full-Service Branch, With A Counter, Will Call Pickup And Stocked Inventory IN An On-Site Warehouse. As One Of Graybar's North American Locations, Our Services Include Lighting Maintenance, Professional Turnkey Lighting Upgrades, And Retrofit, Rollout And Remodel Programs. We Offer One Of The Widest Selections Of Energy-Efficient Lamps And Ballasts, Lighting Control Systems, And Various Led Products. IN Addition To That, Our Knowledgeable Team Of Greenville Electrical Supply Professionals Are Here To Help You Choose The Best Products For Your Lighting Projects. We Are There For You For The Duration Of Your Project And Beyond For Future Maintenance OR Upgrades. There Are A Few Reasons You May Want To Consider Our Electrical Supply Services, And Specifically, A New Commercial Lighting Installation. Do You Feel Like You'Re Spending Too Much Money On Your Energy Bill? Are You Concerned About Energy Efficiency? Are You Confused On What Energy Rebates And Incentives You May Be Eligible For? This Is Where The Experienced Lighting Professionals At Graybar Greenville Can Help. This Type Of Investment Can Save You Money, Add Value To Your Business And Improvement The Environment Of Your Business. How? Well We Offer A Wide Range Of Energy-Efficient Products And Services Designed To Help You Save Time, Money And Energy. Our Ultimate Goal Is To Help You Add Value To Your Business By Designing And Deploying A Custom, Energy Efficient Lighting Installation That Cuts Down On Maintenance And Improves The Environment For The Occupants IN Your Building OR Facility. We Know That Your Projects Are Time Sensitive And Require The Most Professional Services And Reliable Products Available. That's Exactly What We'Ve Been Offering Since 1869 And It's What Has Earned The Company A Reputation For Reliability.

Company Description: Specialty Polymers Is A Family-Owned And Operated Company That Provides Environment-Friendly And Water-Based Emulsion Polymers. Established IN 1969, The Company Offers Polymers For Industrial And Architectural Coatings. It Provides Waterproof And Flexible Wall Mastics Elastomeric Polymers. The Company Offers A Range Of Polymers For Wood And Masonry Substrates. Specialty Polymers Provides Polymers With Efflourescence And Chemical Resistance And Ultraviolet Durability. The Company Also Offers Adhesives For Millwork, Furniture, Kitchen Cabinets And Plywood. It Provides Adhesives For Substrates, Such As Melamine And Vinyl Overlaid Surfaces. The Company Also Offers Emulsion Polymers, Including Styrene And Vinyl Acrylics And Polyvinyl Acetates For The Paper Industry. It Additionally Provides Paperboard Coating And Digital Printing Services. Specialty Polymers Maintains Offices IN Chester, S.C., And Woodburn, Ore.
